ck costars offer Stern a window into midcentury American racial fantasy and the efforts of Black performers to disrupt it. This book incorporates testimony from Davis’s Black contemporaries, including James Baldwin and C. L. R. James, as well as the African American fans who penned letters to Warner Brothers praising Davis’s work. A unique combination of history, star study, and memoir, Bette Davis Black and White allows us to contemplate cross-racial spectatorship in new ways.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aAfrican American motion picture actors and actresseszUnited States. 0aAfrican Americans in motion pictures. 0aAfrican Americans in the motion picture industryzUnited States. 0aMotion picture actors and actresseszUnited States. 0aRace in motion pictures. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / General.2bisacsh  aBette Davis, African American actors, Racism, Racial fantasy, Anti-racism, Ernest Anderson, Hattie McDaniel, Stymie Beard, Blackface masquerade, Hollywood Canteen.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts 2021z9783110753790oZDB-23-DPK08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2021 Englishz978311075403208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073919040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226813721423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226813721/original  a978-3-11-073919-0  University of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075403-2  EBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2021 Englishb2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DPKb2021